Question:

Can we use the sacroiliac joint on the pelvis to determine sex in modern humans?

Data

library(geomorph)
## Loading required package: rgl
## Loading required package: ape
pelves <- readland.nts("~/Downloads/human_left_pelves_2 (3).dta")
classifiers <- read.csv("~/Documents/Classifiers_Sex.csv", header = TRUE, sep = ",")

Size and Shape

gdf <- geomorph.data.frame(GPA_pelves, sex = classifiers$Sex)
Allo <- procD.allometry(coords~Csize, ~sex, data = gdf, iter=499)
##

Visualization

anotherplot <- data.frame(PC1 = PCA$pc.summary$x[,"PC1"], PC2 = PCA$pc.summary$x[,"PC2"], sex = classifiers$Sex)

library(ggplot2)
ggplot(anotherplot, aes(x = PC1, y = PC2, color=sex)) + geom_point() + theme_bw()
